==English==
===Noun===
'''fundamentalism'''

# (''religion'') The tendency to reduce a religion to its most fundamental tenets, based on strict interpretation of core texts.
# (''finance'') The belief that fundamental financial quantities are the best predictor of the price of an instrument.
# (''Christian Movement'') Originally referred to an American Christian movement that began as a response to the rejection of the accuracy of the Bible, the deity of Christ, Christ's atonement for humanity, the virgin birth, and miracles. These points were first affirmed by the PCUSA in its 1910 Minutes of the General Assembly and in a book series entitled "The Fundamentals: A Testimony to the Truth."

